label: A_tI2_139_a-002
title: Pa ($A_{a}$) Structure
comments:
This is an example of a body-centered tetragonal (bct) lattice, a distortion of the \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cI2_229_a-001}{bcc lattice}. 
 \href{current_web_home_dir/A_tI2_139_a-001}{$A6$} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A_tI2_139_a-002}{$A_{a}$} structures have the same AFLOW prototype label, A\_tI2\_139\_a. They are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files. When $c/a=\sqrt{2/3}\approx 0.861$ the coordination number of this system is 10.  In Pa the $c/a$ ratio is 0.823. 
 We take our data from (Zachariasen, 1959), but the ICSD entry is from the later work of (Benedict, 1982).
